songs.title: Roses (MTV Unplugged)
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
It's not that I'm afraid I'm not enough for her
It's not that I can't find the words to say
But when she's with him, she seems happier
And I don't want to take that away

[Pre-Chorus]
And how many times will I see your face?
How many times will you walk away?
Oh, I just have to let you know

[Chorus]
That I'm not tryna start a fire, with this flame
But I'm worried that your heart might feel the same
And I have to be honest with you baby
Tell me if I'm wrong, and this is crazy
But I got you this rose
And I need to know
Will you let it die or let it grow?
No no, hey

[Verse 2]
It's not that I don't care about the love you have, yeah
It's not that I don't want to see you smile, woah
But there's no way that he can feel the same, no no no no
'Cause when I think of you, my mind goes wild

[Pre-Chorus]
And how many times will I see your face?
How many times will you walk away?
Oh, I just have to let you know
Sing it out

[Chorus]
And I'm not tryna start a fire, with this flame, yeah
But I'm worried that your heart might feel the same
And I have to be honest with you baby
Tell me if I'm wrong, and this is crazy
But I got you this rose
And I need to know
Say it
Will you let it die or let it grow?

[Bridge]
You can tell me stop, if you already know
Though I'm not sure my heart can take it
But the look on your face says, don't let me go, no

[Chorus]
I'm not tryna start a fire, with this flame
But I'm worried that your heart might feel the same
And I have to be honest with you baby
Tell me if I'm wrong, and this is crazy
But I got you this rose
And I need to know
Scream it out!
Will you let it die or let it grow?
I'm not tryna start a fire, with this flame
But I'm worried that your heart, it might feel the same
Tell me if I'm wrong, this is crazy
But I got you this rose
And I need to know
Will you let it die?
Will you let it die or let it grow?

[Outro]
Oh, no no
Thank you
